    "body": "### Problem\n\nProblem:\nAfter upgrading to Neovim 0.12 nightly on macOS, vertical split rendering is corrupted when scrolling one window. The left window redraws incorrectly / appears visually shifted or messed up.\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Run `nvim --clean`\n2. Open any long file\n3. Run `:vsplit`\n4. Focus the right window\n5. Scroll in the right window\n6. Observe the left window redraw/render corruption\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nScrolling one split should not visually corrupt the other split.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-2664+g256811a617\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS version: 26.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\ntar",
